Without a doubt Lavelle Crawford is an amazing comedian! From Def Comedy Jam, to Comic View, to Last Comic Standing, he delivers pure laughter. The first time I watched Shaquille O'Neal Presents: All Star Comedy Jam - Live from South Beach and Martin Lawrence Presents: 1st Amendment Stand-Up - Season 3 I literally died laughing from Lavelle parts in those and my lungs almost gave out because it was all fresh material in those two. This DVD, however, is the absolute opposite. He recycled the material in which he used in that Shaq's special and another stand up. There are very few laughs to be had here if you already viewed all his previous material. The material I did not hear before wasn't particularly funny either. The last 10/15 minutes of this Stand-Up was funny however. Another thing I noticed is that they censored some of his curse words, like the F word, but some parts, they allow it. If you never watched a Lavelle Crawford stand-up before, this shouldn't be a big deal to you. But if you want the best out of him, I encourage you to check him out in the Shaquille's DVD special I listed above. The jokes he re-used here are 100x funnier in that stand-up. I was ecstatic to check this DVD out...but sorry, this sucked in my opinion.
